        <para>Example: Tighten four M6 x 12 pulley bolts to standard torque. What is the size and standard torque for
            these four bolts?
        </para>
        <para>M6 x 12 refers to the bolts thread diameter and length. These bolts have a thread diameter of 6 mm and are
            12 mm long.
        </para>
        <para>To find the standard torque for a M6 x 12 bolt look at the torque chart above. We see the standard torque
            for a 6 mm thread diameter class 10.9 bolt should be 13 N&#183;m (115 lbf&#183;in).
        </para>
